{
  "texts": [
    "The smoothness property allows us to approximate each local function f P by a simple discretization,",
    "One could also use other approximations for this step, such as Fourier approximation or polynomial approximation.",
    "In fact, we apply a Fourier approximation instead in the numerical experiments, as discussed in Supplementary Section 4.",
    "For simplicity of the proof, we consider a discretization-based approximation with δ 2 = Θ(1/ϵ) in the definition of T x 0,P to incur at most an OðϵÞ error.",
    "The point is that, for a sufficiently smooth function f P (x) that depends only on coordinates in I P and a sufficiently fine lattice over the coordinates in I P, replacing x by the nearest lattice point (based only on coordinates in I P) causes only a small error."
  ]
}